Homosexuality was decriminalised in China in 1997, but they claim that discrimination against LGBT people has spread.
Because of the country's conservative values, studies estimate that between 70 and 90 percent of men who have sex with other men will eventually marry women.
Many of the transmission of the disease comes from inadequate sexual protection in these relationships.
