The Global Citizen Festival, which began in 2012, is an extension of the Global Poverty Project, an international support group that hopes to end poverty by increasing the number of people who actively fight it.
In order to receive a free ticket to the event (unless you want to pay for a VIP ticket), the audience attending had to complete a series of tasks or "actions", such as volunteering, sending an email to a world leader, making a phone call or any other meaningful way to help raise awareness about their goal of ending poverty.
But what is the success rate of Global Citizen 12 years after it achieved its goal?
